verses.text:
When I am distressed sin, At, without any aid of me or thought
There seems no hope in me, Lord, but thy heart in me;
Take all my sin away, Take all my sin away.

When Christ my Savior knows my case, Salvation's in me;
Burdens were taken hence, He answers my prayer;
Take all my sin away, Take all my sin away.

My stubborn heart he can renew, And make me whole;
Ty gracious spirit will shine through, And sanctify my soul;
Take all my sin away, Take all my sin away.
